etb / edittoolbar             Opens an 'edit' window for a toolbar button

   Format:
      ;etb <name>             View settings for the toolbar button <name>

   Notes:
      Toolbar buttons are used in many 'internal' windows, especially 'main'
         windows. When used, the same set of buttons are used each time.
      Use the ';listtoolbar' command to show the toolbar buttons used, or use
         this command to view settings for a particular button.
      Toolbar buttons can be added, deleted and modified in the client's
         preference window (use the ';editclient' command).

   User commands:
      etb / edittool / edittoolbar
